   <note>This document is a letter dated April 23, 1839, from A. J. Lenoir to Charles F. Welcker in Roane County, TN. Lenoir informs Welcker that his brother George has taken ill and is believed to have scarlet fever. He asks Charles to come soon to visit his brother.</note>
